Detailed Description

cvmx_pko_reg_gmx_port_mode

Notes: The system has a total of 2 + 4 + 4 ports and 2 + 1 + 1 engines (GM0 + PCI + LOOP). This CSR sets the number of GMX0 ports and amount of local storage per engine. It has no effect on the number of ports or amount of local storage per engine for PCI and LOOP. When both GMX ports are used (MODE0=3), each GMX engine has 10kB of local storage. Increasing MODE0 to 4 decreases the number of GMX ports to 1 and increases the local storage for the one remaining PKO GMX engine to 20kB. MODE0 value 0, 1, and 2, or greater than 4 are illegal.

MODE0 GMX0 PCI LOOP GMX0 PCI LOOP ports ports ports storage/engine storage/engine storage/engine 3 2 4 4 10.0kB 2.5kB 2.5kB 4 1 4 4 20.0kB 2.5kB 2.5kB
